overview:
Dungeon Innovations is a software and systems engineering company that creates and serves mobile, cloud, and data sciences integrated products and solutions for key major vertical markets and key economic, social, technological, and behavioral trends.

It operates with crucial and strategic partnerships and advocacy at its core, from the very beginning. These has far-reaching economic, social, technological, and behavioral impact that is very difficult to measure but is true nonetheless.

For example, Dungeon Innovations (along with its parent company, Javasparks Software And Systems) has important ties and collaboration with NASA (National Aeronautics And Space Administration). Through this, we have championed, led, and pioneered with them the International Space Apps Challenge from the very beginning, through virtual mass collaboration to actual site operations. The event has global challenges at its heart with vast impact in earth sciences, economics, space sciences, and space exploration. Dungeon also has key competencies in open data, software, and API’s that NASA uses and publishes.

Dungeon Innovations has key competencies and partnerships that are, as of yet, unparalleled in its base of operation.

Among them are the following:

Key strategic solutions and technical partnership with Amazon and Amazon Web Services Ecosystem; OpenStack founding member, contributor, and country user group leaders, and cloud stack experts; 10gen partnership for software, solutions, channel sales, and services; Cloudera Platform Partnership; Google Cloud Platform service providers; Appcelerator Platform service providers; and others to name a few.

Among key technical expertise and competence of the group are the following: Apple Mac OS X and iOS development expertise; multi-channel, multi-API, and cross-device capabilities with Android ecosystem; HTML 5 Ecosystem expertise; Amazon Web Services Ecosystem; OpenStack Cloud Infrastructure Software; Google Cloud Platform; Big Data, Data Sciences, Historical and Predictive Analytics, Data Warehousing, And Distributed Data Platforms; and others.
